Removing "more citations needed template" from 2018, as the page appears generally well-referenced now.
Reverting removal of reference to disputed ethnic Greek/Turkish heritage. There are sources that claim that Turgut was both Turkish and Greek, we should not exclude either one.

Reverting change of main image - this was previously discussed and consensus was achieved. The image of Dragut's monument in a public square with his palm resting on the globe is more unique to him and indicative of his achievements and stature than the small bust with the orange background of which there are many similar busts at the Istanbul Naval Museum.

Specifically, Balbi (2011) writes that he "was known to his fellow Moslems as 'The Drawn Sword of Islam'"; while Sabatini (2008) writes that he "was dubbed by the Faithful "The Drawn Sword of Islam"". Anyway, i don't have a problem with how you rephrased it; my elaboration meant to be a compromise for removing his religious affiliation.
